# Animations Guide

This portfolio uses several animation systems to create engaging visual effects.

## Animation Components
- [src/components/TextAnimation.tsx](mdc:src/components/TextAnimation.tsx) - Text animation components
- [src/components/ShapeAnimation.tsx](mdc:src/components/ShapeAnimation.tsx) - SVG shape animations
- [src/components/SwissMotion.tsx](mdc:src/components/SwissMotion.tsx) - Swiss design-inspired motion
- [src/components/ScrollReveal.tsx](mdc:src/components/ScrollReveal.tsx) - Scroll-triggered animations
- [src/components/ParallaxLayer.tsx](mdc:src/components/ParallaxLayer.tsx) - Parallax scrolling effects
- [src/components/StaggerItem.tsx](mdc:src/components/StaggerItem.tsx) - Staggered animation sequences

## Animation Utilities
- [src/utils/animations.ts](mdc:src/utils/animations.ts) - Animation utility functions and configs
- [src/hooks/useScrollAnimation.ts](mdc:src/hooks/useScrollAnimation.ts) - Hook for scroll-based animations

## CSS Animations
- [src/app/animations.css](mdc:src/app/animations.css) - CSS animation definitions

## Technology
This project primarily uses Framer Motion for animations combined with the React Intersection Observer library for triggering animations on scroll.
